	(18421,'_transient_dash_4077549d03da2e451c8b5f002294ff51','<div class=\"rss-widget\"><ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.org/news/2013/11/wordpress-3-8-beta-1/\' title=\'The first beta of the 3.8 is now available, and the next dates to watch out for are code freeze on December 5th and a final release on December 12th. 3.8 brings together several of the features as plugins projects and while this isn’t our first rodeo, expect this to be more beta than usual. […]\'>WordPress 3.8 Beta 1</a> <span class=\"rss-date\">November 21, 2013</span><div class=\'rssSummary\'>The first beta of the 3.8 is now available, and the next dates to watch out for are code freeze on December 5th and a final release on December 12th. 3.8 brings together several of the features as plugins projects and while this isn’t our first rodeo, expect this to be more beta than usual. […]</div></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.org/news/2013/10/wordpress-3-7-1/\' title=\'WordPress 3.7.1 is now available! This maintenance release addresses 11 bugs in WordPress 3.7, including: Images with captions no longer appear broken in the visual editor. Allow some sites running on old or poorly configured servers to continue to check for updates from WordPress.org. Avoid fatal errors with certain plugins that were incorrectly calling some […]\'>WordPress 3.7.1 Maintenance Release</a> <span class=\"rss-date\">October 29, 2013</span><div class=\'rssSummary\'>WordPress 3.7.1 is now available! This maintenance release addresses 11 bugs in WordPress 3.7, including: Images with captions no longer appear broken in the visual editor. Allow some sites running on old or poorly configured servers to continue to check for updates from WordPress.org. Avoid fatal errors with certain plugins that were incorrectly calling som [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div>','no'),
